                                                    BUSINESS QUESTION
What behaviors indicate a customer is about to stop purchasing?

                                      QUERY
SELECT
CASE
WHEN days_since_last_purchase > 30 THEN 'at risk'
ELSE 'Active'
END AS Customers_Level,
ROUND(AVG(login_frequency),2) avg_login,
ROUND(AVG(total_purchases),2) avg_purchases,
ROUND(AVG(email_open_rate),2) avg_email_opening,
ROUND(AVG(social_media_engagement_score),2) avg_social_media_engagement,
ROUND(AVG(mobile_app_usage),2)avg_mobile_usage
FROM ecommerce_data
GROUP BY Customers_Level;

INSIGHT:
Customers at risk show lower login frequency, lower engagement, and fewer purchases. This shows a gradual drop-in activity before they stop buying.

RECOMMENDATION
We need to re-engage these customers early by creating awareness and giving incentives like loyalty rewards, limited-time offers to bring them back
before they fully stop purchasing.
